quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  12,53,"‘Yet I do not absolve my [own carnal] soul, for the [carnal] soul indeed prompts [men] to evil, except inasmuch as my Lord has mercy. Indeed my Lord is all-forgiving, all-merciful.’"
  12,54,"The king said, ‘Bring him to me, I will make him my favourite.’ Then, when he had spoken with him, he said, ‘Indeed today [onwards] you will be honoured and trustworthy with us.’"
  12,55,"He said, ‘Put me in charge of the country’s granaries. I am indeed fastidious [and]well-informed.’"
  12,56,"That is how We established Joseph in the land that he may settle in it wherever he wished. We confer Our mercy on whomever We wish, and We do not waste the reward of the virtuous"
  12,57,And the reward of the Hereafter is surely better for those who have faith and are Godwary
  12,58,"[After some years] the brothers of Joseph came and entered his presence. He recognized them, but they did not recognize him"
  12,59,"When he had furnished them with their provision, he said, ‘Bring me a brother that you have through your father. Do you not see that I give the full measure and that I am the best of hosts"
  12,60,"But if you do not bring him to me, then there will be no rations for you with me, and don’t [ever] come near me.’"
  12,61,"They said, ‘We will solicit him from his father. [That] we will surely do.’"
  12,62,"He said to his servants, ‘Put their money [back] into their saddlebags. Maybe they will recognize it when they return to their folks, and maybe they will come back [again].’"
  12,63,"So when they returned to their father, they said, ‘Father, the measure has been withheld from us, so let our brother go with us so that we may obtain the measure, and we will indeed take [good] care of him.’"